intro: Tarenna catanduanensis, commonly known as the Catanduanes tarenna, is a flowering plant native to the Philippines. It belongs to the Rubiaceae family, which includes coffee and gardenias. The plant is characterized by its simple, opposite leaves and small, clustered flowers with four petals. It typically grows in moist, shaded environments within its native habitat. Due to its limited distribution and habitat specificity, it is considered a rare and potentially endangered species.
